<h3>Pause (2012)</h3>

<p>
Short film exploring caste barriers in teenage love.
</p>

</div>


<div class="film">

<h3>Terawa (2013)</h3>

<p>
Film on superstition, caste, and contradictions in marginalized communities.
</p>

</div>


<div class="film">

<h3>Enlighten (2015)</h3>

<p>
Film examining internal caste conflict and Ambedkarite consciousness.
</p>

</div>

</section>


<section>

<h2>Mission</h2>

<p>
Our camera is our weapon. Like the ektara of Dalit folk artists, cinema becomes a tool to challenge caste, preserve anti-caste histories, and build an egalitarian society.
</p>

<p>
We create documentaries, short films, and digital content in Marathi and Hindi to reach wider audiences and strengthen anti-caste movements.
</p>

</section>


